About Veronica Acker, FNP-C

With over 12 years of experience in oncology, I have had the privilege of caring for patients and families through some of the most challenging times in their lives. That experience taught me invaluable lessons in compassion, empathy, and the power of connection, which continue to guide my approach to patient care today.

In 2017, I pursued my Nurse Practitioner education through Chamberlain University, building on my years of clinical experience to expand the ways I could serve my patients. Over the past five years, I have worked in diverse healthcare settings, including weight loss and wellness clinics, chiropractic and integrative practices, primary care, and urgent care. Each role strengthened my understanding of how lifestyle, prevention, and whole-body balance are essential to lasting wellness.

My passion lies in changing lives through education and empowerment — helping patients create sustainable, healthy lifestyles that prevent chronic disease and support long-term vitality. As a graduate of Functional Medicine University with a certification in Functional Medicine, I integrate both conventional and root-cause approaches to uncover the underlying factors contributing to illness.

My goal is to help patients not just manage symptoms, but to heal, restore balance, and thrive. At PureLife Wellness, I am honored to walk alongside each patient on their journey toward optimal health — offering compassionate, evidence-based, and personalized care that supports the mind, body, and spirit.

Functional & Root-Cause Approach

Integrating modern medicine with functional strategies to uncover the “why” behind illness.

Compassionate, Personalized Care

Every patient is seen, heard, and supported as a whole person—mind, body, and spirit.

Education & Empowerment

Guiding patients to take control of their health with knowledge, prevention, and confidence.

Veronica Acker, FNP-C

Functional Medicine Nurse Practitioner

12+ Years Experience Functional Medicine Certified
500+ Patients Helped
4.9/5 Patient Satisfaction
